The key argument against separability is therefore status in itself is derived
 from a collection of items - thus the idea of every item imparting a certain
 utility and combining them often makes little sense.
 To model the group of conspicuous items is to model the mechanism that
 indicates status - which is indicated by consumers to associate themselves
 to a richer (or high status) group of individuals through expenditure (this
 view of status consumption derives from the literature on snob and bandwagon
